<subSubSection id="C368657AFF94FFD192CAEC5F1365FC4D" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF94FFD192CAEC5F130AFDAC" blockId="18.[136,1452,554,905]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF94FFD192CAEC5F1619FD81" bold="true" box="[136,292,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Distribution:</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF94FFD1930AEC5F16B1FD81" box="[328,396,554,580]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it occurs in almost the entire country with the exception of some states of the Northeast (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF94FFD1972CEC5F160FFDAD" author="Flora do Brasil" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" refId="ref20723" refString="Flora do Brasil (2020) under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed 10 August 2019)" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF94FFD192E9EC3B17D3FDAD" box="[171,238,590,616]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In ParNa Iguaçu it occurs in the Céu Azul and Foz do Iguaçu areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF94FFD192FFEC07126EFD75" blockId="18.[136,1452,554,905]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF94FFD192FFEC071688FD49" bold="true" box="[189,437,626,652]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Reproductive period</emphasis>
: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF94FFD19023EC071458FD49" author="Sartori, A. L. B. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A." box="[609,869,626,652]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" pagination="211 - 246" refId="ref23158" refString="Sartori, A. L. B. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A. (1998) As especies de Machaerium Pers. (Leguminosae-Papilionoideae-Dalbergieae) ocorrentes no estado de Sao Paulo. Revista Brasileira de Botanica 21: 211 - 246. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0100 - 84041998000300001" type="journal article" year="1998">Sartori &amp; Tozzi (1998)</bibRefCitation>
this species flowers from November to March and fruits from March to June. In ParNa Iguaçu it was found in flower and fruit in March and only in fruit in July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF94FFD192FFECCF15D7FCD9" blockId="18.[136,1452,554,905]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF94FFD192FFECCF16C4FD11" bold="true" box="[189,505,698,724]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Diagnostic characteristics:</emphasis>
The genus is recognized by its arboreal habit with alternate leaflets, samara fruits and seeds with basal position. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF94FFD193E9ECAA1526FD3D" authorityName="Stellfeld" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Vellozo" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[427,539,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Machaerium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF94FFD193E9ECAA1526FD3D" box="[427,539,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">M. hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its narrow oblong leaflets, up to 58 per leaf, pairs of nodal and internodal prickles and samaras with an obovate wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF94FFD192FFED5316D2FC85" blockId="18.[136,1452,554,905]" box="[189,495,806,832]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF94FFD192FFED53165AFC85" bold="true" box="[189,359,806,832]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Conservation:</emphasis>
Native-NE.
</paragraph>
